Deployment Documentation:

1-Environment Setup:
    PythonAnywhere account created
    Virtual environment set up
    MySQL database created
2-Configuration:
    settings.py updated for production and MySQL
    WSGI file configured
    Environment variables set in PythonAnywhere
3-Database:
    MySQL database created and configured
    Migrations applied
4-Static Files:
    Collected and served through PythonAnywhere's static file serving
5-Maintenance:
    Update code: Pull from Git, update requirements, migrate if needed
    Monitor app: Check error logs in PythonAnywhere dashboard
    Database backups: Use MySQL Workbench or phpMyAdmin for backups
6-Scaling:
PythonAnywhere free tier has limitations. For scaling, consider upgrading to a paid plan or migrating to a more scalable platform in the future.